@@ -0,0 +1,109 @@
+# AnkiDroid JS API - Tag Management Functions
+
+This document describes the new tag management functions added to the AnkiDroid JavaScript API.
+
+## New Functions
+
+### 1. `ankiSetNoteTags(noteId, tags)`
+
+Sets/replaces all tags for a specific note. This follows REST API design principles where you manipulate the entire tag set.
+
+**Parameters:**
+- `noteId` (number): The ID of the note to modify
+- `tags` (array of strings): An array of tag names to set on the note
+
+**Returns:** 
+- A promise that resolves to an API result object with `success: true` if successful
+
+**Example:**
+```javascript
+const api = AnkiDroidJS.init({
+    developer: "your-email@example.com",
+    version: "0.0.3"
+});
+
+// Set tags (replaces all existing tags)
+await api.ankiSetNoteTags(noteId, ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"]);
+
+// Remove all tags by passing an empty array
+await api.ankiSetNoteTags(noteId, []);
+```
+
+### 2. `ankiGetTagsFromNote(noteId)`
+
+Retrieves all tags from a specific note as a JSON array.
+
+**Parameters:**
+- `noteId` (number): The ID of the note to query
+
+**Returns:** 
+- A promise that resolves to an API result object containing a JSON array of tag strings
+
+**Example:**
+```javascript
+const api = AnkiDroidJS.init({
+    developer: "your-email@example.com",
+    version: "0.0.3"
+});
+
+// Get tags from a note
+const result = await api.ankiGetTagsFromNote(noteId);
+// result.value will be a JSON array like: ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"]
+const tags = JSON.parse(result.value);
+console.log(tags); // ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3"]
+```
+
+## Use Cases
+
+### Remove a specific tag from a note
+
+```javascript
+// Get current tags
+const result = await api.ankiGetTagsFromNote(noteId);
+const currentTags = JSON.parse(result.value);
+
+// Remove a specific tag
+const newTags = currentTags.filter(tag => tag !== "tagToRemove");
+
+// Set the updated tags
+await api.ankiSetNoteTags(noteId, newTags);
+```
+
+### Add a tag only if it doesn't exist
+
+```javascript
+// Get current tags
+const result = await api.ankiGetTagsFromNote(noteId);
+const currentTags = JSON.parse(result.value);
+
+// Add tag if not present
+if (!currentTags.includes("newTag")) {
+    currentTags.push("newTag");
+    await api.ankiSetNoteTags(noteId, currentTags);
+}
+```
+
+### Replace multiple tags at once
+
+```javascript
+// Get current tags
+const result = await api.ankiGetTagsFromNote(noteId);
+const currentTags = JSON.parse(result.value);
+
+// Replace old tags with new ones
+const updatedTags = currentTags.map(tag => {
+    if (tag === "old1") return "new1";
+    if (tag === "old2") return "new2";
+    return tag;
+});
+
+await api.ankiSetNoteTags(noteId, updatedTags);
+```
+
+## Notes
+
+- Tags are automatically canonified (sorted alphabetically) by AnkiDroid when saved
+- Empty tag strings are ignored
+- Tag names are case-sensitive
+- These functions follow REST API design principles: `GET` to retrieve the full set, `SET` to replace the full set
+
